{"id": "firmware-development--rp2040-lora-hf-firmware", "title": "RP2040-Lora-HF firmware", "forum": "firmware-development", "messages": [{"id": "1474453545741717716", "author": "Tony", "author_handle": "tonyvincz", "user_id": "1439248652672696322", "avatar": "", "timestamp": "Friday, February 20, 2026 12:11 p.m.", "timestamp_short": "2026-02-20 12:11 p.m.", "text": "Hi, I built a new firmware for the following board https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/B0CSYYL38D?ref=ppx_yo2ov_dt_b_fed_asin_title The RPI Pico 2040 + WaveShare SX1261 firmware isn't good for this module, because the radio PIN's are different. How can I share this fw version? Regards Tony", "content_html": "<div class=\"chatlog__content chatlog__markdown\"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve>Hi,\n\nI built a new firmware for the following board\n\n<a href=\"https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/B0CSYYL38D?ref=ppx_yo2ov_dt_b_fed_asin_title\">https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/B0CSYYL38D?ref=ppx_yo2ov_dt_b_fed_asin_title</a>\n\nThe RPI Pico 2040 + WaveShare SX1261 firmware isn&#39;t good for this module, because the radio PIN&#39;s are different.\n\nHow can I share this fw version?\n\nRegards\n\nTony</span></div>", "embeds_html": ["<div class=chatlog__embed><div class=\"chatlog__embed-color-pill chatlog__embed-color-pill--default\"></div><div class=chatlog__embed-content-container><div class=chatlog__embed-content><div class=chatlog__embed-text><div class=chatlog__embed-title><a class=chatlog__embed-title-link href=\"https://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/B0CSYYL38D?ref=ppx_yo2ov_dt_b_fed_asin_title\"><div class=\"chatlog__markdown chatlog__markdown-preserve\">LoRa Development Board Kit Based on Raspberry Pi RP2040 Microcontro...</div></a></div><div class=chatlog__embed-description><div class=\"chatlog__markdown chatlog__markdown-preserve\">Overview\n RP2040-LoRa-HF is a LoRa development board using the new generation of SX1262 RF chip, provides better performance than the SX127X series in power consumption, communication distance and p